summary: This is an email from a Southwest Airlines litigation specialist to the FBI, transmitting documents responsive to a grand jury subpoena related to Ghislaine Maxwell. The email states that Southwest produced travel records from its CIRRUS database but was unable to locate records for Ghislaine Maxwell and notes that their records retention only goes back 10 years.

persons.name: Ghislaine Maxwell
persons.context: Named as the subject of a grand jury subpoena for travel records; also referenced by the alias Ghislaine Borgerson. Southwest Airlines states they were unable to locate responsive records for her.

events.title: Southwest Airlines Responds to Grand Jury Subpoena
events.description: A Southwest Airlines litigation specialist emails the FBI to transmit documents responsive to a grand jury subpoena related to Ghislaine Maxwell. The email includes produced documents and a declaration of custodian of records.

keyFacts: Southwest Airlines produced documents from its CIRRUS database in response to a grand jury subpoena related to Ghislaine Maxwell.
Southwest Airlines was unable to locate any responsive travel records for Ghislaine Maxwell (also known as Ghislaine Borgerson).
Southwest Airlines' records retention policy for travel records only extends back 10 years, meaning they would not have records prior to January 28, 2010.
The produced documents were bates numbered SWA000001 to SWA000008 and included an executed Declaration of Custodian of Records.
